    <name>
      <text>Finding the midpoint</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>In the figure below, \(ABC\) is a triangle where \(M\) is the midpoint of \(AC\) and \(N\) is the midpoint of \(AB\).</p>
[[jsxgraph]]
var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, {
    /* Increased bounding box to 22 to fit coordinates up to 20 comfortably */
    boundingbox: [-2, 22, 22, -2],
    axis: true,
    showCopyright: false
});

var A = board.create('point', [{#ax#}, {#ay#}], {name:'A', fixed:true, size:2});
var B = board.create('point', [{#bx#}, {#by#}], {name:'B', fixed:true, size:2});
var C = board.create('point', [{#cx#}, {#cy#}], {name:'C', fixed:true, size:2});

var poly = board.create('polygon', [A,B,C], {borders:{strokeColor:'black'}});

/* Visual Helpers */
var M = board.create('midpoint', [A, C], {name:'M', color:'red', size:3});
var N = board.create('midpoint', [A, B], {name:'N', color:'red', size:3});

board.create('segment', [B, M], {dash:2, strokeColor:'gray'});
board.create('segment', [C, N], {dash:2, strokeColor:'gray'});
[[/jsxgraph]]

<p>Determine the coordinates of \(M\) and \(N\).</p>
<p><i>(Enter your answers as coordinates, e.g., <code>[x,y]</code>)</i></p>

<p>\( M = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] </p>
<p>\( N = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]</p>
<p>[[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Method:</b></p>
<p>The midpoint \( (x_m, y_m) \) between two points \( (x_1, y_1) \) and \( (x_2, y_2) \) is calculated by taking the average of their coordinates:</p>
\[ M = \left( \frac{x_1 + x_2}{2}, \frac{y_1 + y_2}{2} \right) \]

<p><b>For point M (Midpoint of AC):</b></p>
\[ x_M = \frac{{@ax@} + {@cx@}}{2} = {@mx@} \]
\[ y_M = \frac{{@ay@} + {@cy@}}{2} = {@my@} \]
<p>So, \( M = {@ta_m@} \).</p>

<p><b>For point N (Midpoint of AB):</b></p>
\[ x_N = \frac{{@ax@} + {@bx@}}{2} = {@nx@} \]
\[ y_N = \frac{{@ay@} + {@by@}}{2} = {@ny@} \]
<p>So, \( N = {@ta_n@} \).</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
